article.headline: Jacksonville St. 73, Reinhardt 62
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- B.J. Spencer had 17 points and six rebounds to lead Jacksonville State to a 73-62 victory over Reinhardt College on Monday. The win snapped a 14-game losing streak for the Gamecocks (5-16). Anthony Wilson had 15 points, Walker Russell had 14 and Tim Lewis had 13. Lewis and Brandon Davis had a game-high 10 rebounds each, and Russell had a game-high 8 assists. The team shot 39 percent from the field and led 31-28 at halftime. Brandon Jennings led Reinhardt (15-8) with a game-high 19 points. He shot 8-of-17 from 3-point range and led the Eagles with 7 rebounds. Chris Jones scored 15 points and Shae Blair had 11. Jones shot 5-of-9 and Blair shot 5-of-11 from 3-point range. The game saw 13 lead changes and 13 ties, but the Gamecocks took the lead for good with 5:54 left on the clock. A Wilson lay-up brought the score to 56-54, and the Gamecocks then went on a 10-2 run over the next four minutes. The Eagles fought to within six points with 55 seconds left in the game, but the Gamcocks hit 7-of-8 from the free throw line over the final minute to seal the win.
